wikipedia_page.main: George Tiernay Mirehouse (11 May 1863 – 5 March 1923) was an English gentleman and amateur cricketer who appeared in 13 first-class cricket matches for Cambridge University, Somerset and the Marylebone Cricket Club in the 1880s. Primarily a right-arm medium-fast bowler, Mirehouse took 22 first-class wickets at an average of 27.54.
